revision.text:
'''929: Tanakh B'yachad''' (Hebrew: Bible Together, 929 - תנך ביחד) is a project for learning one chapter of [[Tanakh]] per day (except Friday and Saturday), totaling 5 chapters per week. The name '929' refers to the total number of chapters in the Tanakh.

The project was announced by the [[Education Ministry (Israel)|Israeli Education Ministry]], and began on December 21, 2014.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.jpost.com/Israel-News/Crack-open-your-Bible-929-day-study-project-begins-in-Jerusalem-385067|title = Crack open your Bible: 929 day study project begins in Jerusalem|last = |first = |date = December 18, 2014|work = |access-date = January 1, 2015|publisher = [[Jerusalem Post]]}}</ref> The first cycle was completed on April 18, 2018, coinciding with Israel's 70th [[Independence Day (Israel)|Independence Day]].<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.ynetnews.com/articles/0,7340,L-4608007,00.html|title = National Bible project launched|last = |first = |date = December 28, 2014|work = |access-date = January 1, 2015|publisher = [[Ynetnews]]}}</ref> 

The first cycle of the project offered content in [[Hebrew]] only. The second cycle, which began on July 15, 2018, offers some content in English as well.<ref> 
{{Cite news|url = https://www.timesofisrael.com/launching-in-english-chapter-a-day-project-looks-to-bring-bible-back-to-masses|title = Launching in English, chapter-a-day project looks to bring Bible back to masses|last = |first = |date = July 15, 2018|work = |access-date = July 16, 2018|publisher = [[The Times of Israel]]}}</ref> It will conclude on February 2, 2022. 

