{{advert|date=September 2015}}
[[Image:Forchiwiki.jpg|right|thumb|277px|Forgotten Chicago logo in the [[Kabel (typeface)|Kabel]] typeface.]]
'''Forgotten Chicago''' is an [[organization]] that seeks to discover and document little known elements of Chicago’s [[infrastructure]], [[architecture]], [[neighborhoods]] and general cityscape, whether existing or historical.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Mission Statement {{!}} Forgotten Chicago {{!}} History, Architecture, and Infrastructure|url = http://forgottenchicago.com/mission-statement/mission-statement/|website = forgottenchicago.com|access-date = 2016-01-15}}</ref>
The organization exposes many of these often overlooked elements of Chicago’s [[built environment]] to a wide audience to increase interest in their [[Historic preservation|preservation]].<ref name="mission">{{cite web|url=http://forgottenchicago.com/intro2.php|title=Forgotten Chicago Mission Statement}}</ref> In addition to conducting research and publishing articles on their website, Forgotten Chicago also leads [[neighborhood]] walking [[tours]]<ref name="tour">{{cite web|url=http://forgottenchicago.com/tour.php|title=Forgotten Chicago Tour No. 1}}</ref> and holds free presentations at area [[libraries]].<ref name="lib">{{cite web|url=http://www.lib.oak-lawn.il.us/adultprograms.aspx|title=Oak Lawn Illinois Public Library adult programs}}</ref> Forgotten Chicago has received many accolades including being named one of ''[[Chicago Magazine]]'''s 171 best [[Chicago]] websites in February 2008<ref name="chimag">{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagomag.com/Chicago-Magazine/February-2008/Nothing-But-Net-171-Great-Chicago-Web-Sites/Just-the-Links-Please|title=Chicago Magazine's List of the 171 Best Chicago Websites}}</ref> and being featured in the ''[[Chicago Tribune]]'',<ref name="chitrib">{{cite news|url=http://featuresblogs.chicagotribune.com/technology_internetcritic/2008/02/forgotten-chica.html|title=The Chicago Tribune Hypertext |author=Steve Johnson | date=February 27, 2008}}</ref> ''The [[Northwest Indiana Times]]'',<ref name="nyit">{{cite web|url=http://www.nwi.com/articles/2009/04/27/community/lake/doc5f5a96a443a804dc862575a2006e1895.txt|title=Historical buildings show business and beauty can coexist.|author=Janet Moran}}</ref> ''[[Time Out (company)|Time Out]] Chicago'',<ref name="TOC">{{cite web|url=http://chicago.timeout.com/articles/museums-culture/77563/forgotten-chicago-documents-secret-aspects-of-the-city|title=Forgotten Chicago documents secret aspects of the City.|author=Jake Malooley}}</ref> and local radio.<ref name="OTL">{{cite web|url=http://www.outsidetheloopradio.com/otl/2009/01/30/otl-episode-123/|title=Chicago: Out of Sight, Out of Mind |author=Outside the Loop RADIO}}</ref>
Their web presence underwent a major re-design in January 2009 with feature improvements, revised and updated content, and more ways for the public to get involved with the organization through [[Twitter]] and [[Facebook]].
